accompanied by up-and-coming kraut/prog rock band Hedersleben. Following what has been widely regarded as the most ambitious album of his career, one that MOJO called "a sprawling but polished album," Space Fusion Odyssey, Turner continues his astonishing career rebirth with a newly reinvigorated sense of musical creativity and sonic exploration.
Frequently called "The Spirit Of Hawkwind," Turner was a major creative force during that group's most critically acclaimed and successful period, 1969-1976. His outlandish costumes, improvised sax and flute playing, and general wild man persona became iconic representations of the band, and we would go on to pen some of their most popular songs including "Brainstorm" and "Master of the Universe." After leaving Hawkwind, Turner used his newfound freedom to travel to Egypt, where he soaked up the history and culture, and also made a recording of his flute music in the King's Chamber of the Great Pyramid of Cheops. In 1985, Turner relocated to the western side of Wales, where he set up a new age community in a fairly rural, isolated area. He has continued to release new music including 2013's Space Gypsy and 2015's Space Fusion Odyssey. A brand new track from his forthcoming studio album premieres on a special 6CD box set called Space Rock: An Interstellar Traveler's Guide. This incredible collection features a diverse sampling of space rock artists young and old including Hawkwind, Amon Düül II, Ozric Tentacles, Gong, Can, Earthling Society, and Hedersleben along with a Hedersleben, a 1970’s style Krautrock band, had its genesis in the German village of the same name in 2012. There, a few kilometers from the historic city of Quedlinburg, Nicky Garratt set up a space to play music in the great tradition of the German rock pioneers. Based now in northern California, the members of Hedersleben have been quite fluid but the dedication to Progressive Rock remains the binding force of the band. 
Aside from the Hedersleben’s three highly acclaimed albums, Upgoer (2013), Die Neuen Welten (2014) and The Fall Of Chronopolis (2015), they have recorded with Hawkwind’s Nik Turner (Space Gypsy), backing him on three US tours, and recorded with Joel Vandroogenbroeck as Brainticket. (Past, Present and Future). 2016 sees the release of Hedersleben 4 – Orbit in time for their fourth national tour.
Alicia Previn / Violin & Vocals
In the early '70s as a young teenager, Alicia (aka Lovely) Previn played in a number of bands associated with The Source Family in Los Angeles, including the infamous Yahowha 13 and also Breath. During the '80s Alicia had a solo career in the UK, releasing a solo LP and several singles before recording with a string of influential artists. Her discography includes recordings by Richard Thompson, General Public, Great White, In Tua Nua, The Communards, Cracker, Andy Leek, Terry Talbot, Ten Bright Spikes, and many more.

Alicia has toured extensively in the US and Europe. She is the daughter of four-time Academy and ten-time Grammy Award-winning conductor, composer, and pianist André Previn, and jazz singer Betty Bennett. 

Jai Young Kim / Keyboards       
Jai Young Kim is a musician, composer, producer, and engineer born in Seoul, South Korea. He’s performed around the world with artists including Secret Chiefs 3, Nik Turner’s Hawkwind, Job, and Species Being. His numerous recording credits include work with the late Steve Mackay (The Stooges) and Scott Thunes (former musical director for Frank Zappa).

Nicky Garratt / Guitars   
Nicky Garratt began a career in music during the progressive rock explosion of the early '70s in England. He studied classical guitar under Katherine Warner, playing Bach at the Leicester Festival of Music in 1975 and 1976. After moving to London, Garratt joined the UK Subs in 1977. National chart and international touring success quickly followed.

After 40 years, Garratt returned to progressive rock as musical director and guitar player for Hawkwind’s Nik Turner and underground Swiss prog legends Brainticket.

Donald “Doc” Miller / Bass Guitar & Vocals 
Los Angeles-born Doc Miller studied guitar, Javanese Gamelan, and music theory at CalArts before moving to the Bay Area in 2007 and putting all into practice in countless west-coast venues. Doc has played in a number of local bands, including Whatfunlifewas, Lysine, Dead Man, and several projects with drummer John Daren Thomas.

John Daren Thomas / Drums & Percussion
John Daren Thomas earned a bachelor’s degree in Percussion from Humboldt State University, then continued his studies at the University of Ghana in West Africa, and has since been to 21 different countries pursuing new and exotic sounds and rhythms.

John grew up around progressive music royalty: His father, also John, is a well known live/session keyboardist, and was a member of Captain Beefheart’s Magic Band, Mallard, and Sparks, among others.


Garratt: We watched Vagabunden Karawane, the Embryo documentary, and I was absolutely mesmerized by the theme music, which we then played together as an extended jam. When in 2012 Garratt became the music director for Hawkwind's Nik Turner the opportunity to reunite with drummer Jason Willer - both were former members of UK Subs of which Garratt was a founder, co-writer and producer (1977 – 1983 and again 1996 – 2011) - presented itself. While working on Turners Space Gypsy album the embryonic Hedersleben began to take shape. 
Music: Influenced by the fearless sprit of the early Krautrock scene Hedersleben, augmented by 2nd keyboard player/vocalist Kyrsten Bean, recorded their first album Upgoer in June 2013. Alongside Garratt and Willer, the album features Bryce Shelton from Hollow Mirrors on bass and Kephera Moon from Dragontime on keyboard and vocals. 
Immediately following Upgoer this line-up of Hedersleben recorded with Joel Vandroogenbroeck as the new album of legendary swiss Krautrock band Brainticket. (Album scheduled for 2014 release). 
Touring: Hedersleben completed their first US tour Oct/Nov 2013 both opening for and backing Nik Turner. 


Kephera Moon (keyboards, vocals) is a classically trained musician, composer, and piano instructor. She has recorded with Dragontime, Brainticket and toured with Nik Turner's Hawkwind. 

Bryce Shelton (Bass, vocals), is a musician and visual artist from the SF Bay Area. He is a multi-instrumentalist singer/songwriter. He has recorded with Hollow Mirrors, Brainticket and toured with Nik Turner's Hawkwind. 

Nicky Garratt (Guitar), is an English born musician who studied classical guitar before playing progressive rock in the early 70's. He later formed the seminal British punk band UK Subs. He has also recorded with Nik Turner's Hawkwind and Brainticket. 

Jason Willer (Drums/Percussion), is a SF bay area born musician and singer/songwriter. He is a drum/percussion instructor and seasoned touring artist.
